## State Management — `TurnFillDataService.cs`

**File**: [TurnFillDataService.cs](file:///c:/Users/DELL/Desktop/Coded/intisor/TurnIt/Services/TurnFillDataService.cs)

Acts as the single source of truth for all UI state. Bridges `StorageService` (persistence) and the UI.

### Key Exposed Properties
| Property | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Resources` | `List<Resource>` | UI view of consumables with level, state, and assignee |
| `Members` | `List<RosterParticipant>` | Active roster members mapped from domain `RosterMember` |
| `Rosters` | `List<Roster>` | All rosters in the current space |
| `ActiveRoster` | `Roster?` | Currently selected roster |
| `ActiveScheduleSlots` | `List<RosterSlot>` | 90-day upcoming schedule slots |

### Key Methods
- `InitializeAsync()` / `LoadDataAsync()` — load from IndexedDB, generate slots if needed
- `AddResource(Resource)` — create new consumable + optional initial refill
- `RefillResource(id, date, qty, cost, notes)` — log refill, advance roster slot
- `AddRoster(Roster)` / `SetActiveRoster(Guid)` — multi-roster support
- `AddMember(name)` / `RemoveMember(id)` / `SkipMember(id)` — roster member management
- `UpdateRosterConfig(rotationType, startDate)` — apply config and regenerate slots

