## UI Architecture — Mobile-First (Complete Rebuild June 2026)

All screens are designed **mobile-first (360px baseline)** scaling up with `sm:` breakpoints.

### Layout Rules
- Header: `h-14` (56px), sticky, `z-40`
- Bottom nav: `h-16` with `padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` for notch safety
- Main content: `padding-bottom: calc(4rem + env(safe-area-inset-bottom))` so last card clears the nav
- Touch targets: minimum `min-h-[48px]` / `min-h-[44px]` on all interactive elements
- All overlays are bottom-sheets or full-width right slide-overs — never centered modals
- No `max-w` caps on mobile — everything is edge-to-edge

